 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelerion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elerion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 5:02:53 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PS2 Games...which ones to get?</span><hr size=1> Well, the games I own or have tested for a large amount of time, in order of appearance:<br>
<br>
GT3 - 8/10. Amazing racing game, but that isn't really my favourite genre. Still, it's loads of fun.<br>
<br>
Tekken Tag - 9/10. I simply love Tekken. The learning curve is just great. Newbies can pick it up and have fun, but you can play it for 200 hours and still have more to learn. Playing this against an equal human opponent is just too much fun.<br>
<br>
This is Football 2002 (Soccer, for you americans) - 8/10. Great soccer game, but it's just not the same now that my brother doesn't live at home anymore. Sports games were more fun when I always had a human opponent <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
GTA3 - 10/10. Sooooo much fun. Great &quot;serious&quot; play, as opposed to the first two games, and just messing around is ever more fun than ever too <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   One of those games you never really grow 100% tired of<br>
<br>
Tony Hawk 3 - 9/10. Amazing game, but it's a tiny bit too much like the #2 to really blow me away. I played the prequel a heck of a lot, and this feels more like an expansion than a new game *shrug*. If you haven't played a Tony Hawk game before, buy it right now.<br>
<br>
Jak &amp; Daxter - 8/10. Cool platformer. Somewhere in between Mario64 and Crash Bandicoot. Daxter is a quite hilarious character, and the gameplay is smooth. It has a tendency to get a tiny bit repetitive when you get past 50% though, which is why I never got around to finish it while I borrowed it.<br>
<br>
Devil May Cry - Well, I've only had it a few hours, but so far it seems great. Read my seperate thread for more info.<br>
<br>
I know you have a few of these already, but I found it easier to just list them all when I got started <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
EDIT: FYI, Final Fantasy X won't be released in Europe until February, but I'll be all over it on release day <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelerion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elerion</A> at: 12/21/01 5:05:32 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzulian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zulian</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif " BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 5:17:39 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://members.aol.com/Rhinoblast/Tornear.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PS2 Games...which ones to get?</span><hr size=1> Tekken Tag is great, I love Tekken Bowl, best mini game ever :P <p>"I'm not dumb. I just have a command of thoroughly useless information." -- Calvin & Hobbes by Bill Watterson 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/upeebs.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Peebs</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 5:41:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PS2 Games...which ones to get?</span><hr size=1> Twisted Metal Black is cool.  I really like Dynasty Warriors 3, but some people get tired of the repetiveness.  I love hacking apart hundreds of troops.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :b --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":b"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uzolendnewbieater.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zolend Newbieater</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.zolendpics.homestead.com/files/Red_Z.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 6:23:38 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: PS2 Games...which ones to get?</span><hr size=1> I thought Tekken Tag was pretty lame, I have it for my PS2 too but I was sort of disapointed by it. Soul Calibur owns it. The moves are way too hard imho, they are really hard to pull off and not very rewarding. I studied for about 5 hours to learn how to pull off Kings 8 throw combo and then it ended up being pretty useless anyway.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ulisboa.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lisboa</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 6:32:35 