But yeah, it's a pretty cool game.  Just don't expect Baldur's Gate, because it's not.  It's a dungeon hack. <p>"I'm not dumb. I just have a command of thoroughly useless information." -- Calvin & Hobbes by Bill Watterson 
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/utameran.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tameran</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/21/01 11:01:29 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re:</span><hr size=1> My opinion is to go out and buy Dead or Alive Hardcore if you don't enjoy Tekken. Its nice to be able to counter and the moves and combos are much easier to do are a much more rewarding. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uelerion.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Elerion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/22/01 9:25:25 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tekken</span><hr size=1> Well, the combos are supposed to be hard to do and not omnipotent to keep Tekken from being a combo based game. Once you get enough skill you will decimate a combo-freak simply by doing fast jabs and kicks. It would be really boring if all the game was about was doing 10-hit combos and multithrows. High level Tekken play is all about timing, reflexes and strategy, not mindless comboing. You can counter in Tekken too, however not all characters can do it, and there are several different counters. That adds more depth in my eyes.<br>
<br>
Point is, DoA is a better game for the gamer that likes to master a game in less than 10 hours of play. It's also really newbie friendly, because button mashers can actually beat experienced players.<br>
Tekken is a much deeper game, with a learning curve. You start out by mashing the buttons, then you learn a few simple combos and blocks to start controlling your game. From there you go on to mastering your character(s) good moves, knowing when to use which, and learning advanced tecniques like juggling, countering, etc. This gives the game extreme long-term potential, as long as you don't mind practicing <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
And of course there is no way to compare AI to a real human opponent.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showMessage?topicID=5284.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.showMessage?topicID=5254.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.emailToFriend?topicID=5275.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.threadControl?topicID=5275.topic><img src=http://www.evercrack.net/shpics/closeThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5275.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehouseoutsidenorrath.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5275.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="thesafehouseloungegeneraldiscussion">Main Lounge<option value="thesafehousecontractsbountiesjobsquestsetc">News Bulletin<option value="thesafehousetrainingstudioqafornewbies">Training Studio<option value="thesafehousethebackroomsecretsspoilers">The Back Alley<option value="thesafehousefrm13">Quests of Norrath<option value="thesafehousetherootcellar">The Root Cellar<option value="thesafeh